  "response": "Yes, money laundering is unlawful. It is a criminal activity that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. The process makes it appear that the money comes from a legitimate source.\n\nMoney laundering is illegal because it allows criminals to profit from their illicit activities, finance further illegal operations, and evade taxes, undermining the integrity of financial systems and economies. Laws and regulations in most jurisdictions require financial institutions and other entities to implement measures to detect and prevent money laundering. Penalties for money laundering can be severe and include substantial fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.",
